{
  "stem": "24163.4",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The backyard had places where they shot people with dried blood still on the ground and a huge hole filled with remnants of human bones taken out of the furnace.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The whole affair had a high stone wall with an electric fence around it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I shall never forget that yard.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And what I witnessed there as long-- will be with me as long as I live.' And it is, believe me. 'Some of the dogs had been taken away, others had been shot.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Like I said, we caught the guards by surprise.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And now, there are dead SS men laying everywhere around the camp, killed either by our troops or some of the inmates who got a hold of their guns.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Justice well done.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I only hope that none got away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "While we entered, General Patch and his staff as well as congressman and newspaper reporters started to look around everywhere.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I hope they can write what they saw and tell people at home about it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I want you to tell all the people you know about this and read the letter I'll write to them to my folks, but not so detailed.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I also visited Munchen and entered remnants of Adolph Hitler's [GERMAN], his old hangout, and looked around town.' And I write about the [GERMAN] and what I saw there, which is anti-climatic, of course, after I read to you my letter about the camp.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I say goodbye to my wife in the letter.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I think that this letter tells it better than even my memory.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Even so, my memory is pretty good about all this.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I walked up to the fence.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the first thing I wanted to do-- I had filled our Jeep with food.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
